### 1. Create Incident
POST http://localhost:5116/api/incident
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "title": "Production API timeout",
  "description": "Users report 504 errors during checkout"
}

### 2. Get All Incidents (to grab the GUID)
GET http://localhost:5116/api/incident

### 3. Add Log Entry #1
# Replace {{GUID}} with the incident ID from step 1
POST http://localhost:5116/api/incidents/{{GUID}}/logs
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "service": "checkout-api",
  "logLevel": "Error",
  "message": "Database timeout while processing payment"
}

### 4. Add Log Entry #2
POST http://localhost:5116/api/incidents/{{GUID}}/logs
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "service": "checkout-api",
  "logLevel": "Critical",
  "message": "Primary database unavailable"
}

### 5. Get Logs for Incident
GET http://localhost:5116/api/incidents/{{GUID}}/logs

### 6. Analyze with AI
POST http://localhost:5116/api/ai/analyze/{{GUID}}

### Expected Result:
# {
#   "severity": "Critical",
#   "rootCause": "Possible issue detected from logs related to 'Production API timeout'.",
#   "suggestedFix": "Review failing dependencies, inspect recent deployments, and increase automated test coverage around the affected flow.",
#   "recommendedTests": [
#     "Add unit tests for the affected service method.",
#     "Add integration tests for the failing workflow.",
#     "Add regression tests covering the reported incident scenario."
#   ]
# }
